[["index.html", "Oracle Cost Survey Metadata Chapter1 Overview 1.1 SSB Cost Survey 1.2 Confidentiality 1.3 Contacts", " Oracle Cost Survey Metadata Samantha Werner, Gregory Ardini, Elizabeth Conley and Tanya Noteva 2024-03-13 Chapter1 Overview This website serves as the official metadata for the SSB cost survey data, databased on Oracle. Currenlty survey data from years 2011, 2012, 2015 are databased on Oracle. 1.1 SSB Cost Survey The Greater Atlantic Region Commercial Fishing Business Cost Survey (commercial fishing cost survey or cost survey for short) is a voluntary cost survey of federally permitted vessel owners in the New England and Mid-Atlantic region of the United States. Two main goals of the survey are to collect fixed and quasi-fixed cost information to generate vessel-level profitability estimates, as well as track economic performance over time to inform management decisions. The survey has been implemented intermittently since 2006. 1.2 Confidentiality Data confidentiality is of the utmost importance. Each individual that accesses the cost data must have a signed non-disclosure agreement which specifies the cost data by name. Data users must be aware of the restrictions with handling Personally Identifiable Information (PII). As a reminder, data cannot be shared through email and must follow the rule of three to protect confidentiality. Data cannot be shared without notifying cost working group staff and obtaining a singed NDA. For any questions or more on the confidentiality of the cost survey data, please contact Samantha Werner (Samantha.Werner@noaa.gov) and Gregory Ardini (Gregory.Ardini@noaa.gov). 1.3 Contacts For questions regarding, the metadata, the Oracle databases(including access), or suggestions, please contact Samantha Werner (Samantha.Werner@noaa.gov) "],["tables-and-views.html", "Chapter2 Tables and Views 2.1 VCS_COMMON_VARIABLES_MV 2.2 VCS_COST2011 2.3 VCS_COST2012 2.4 VCS_COST2015", " Chapter2 Tables and Views 2.1 VCS_COMMON_VARIABLES_MV Description: This view presents common variables collected from the cost survey over time. Values are presented at the annual vessel-level for the year in which they were queried unless otherwise noted (nominal dollars). To be considered a common variable, the variable must appear in two or more cost surveys over time. Given that the survey instrument changed over time, there may be slight discrepancies in the variable over time. Please see the comments for further clarification.The primary key is HULLNUM and SURVEY_YEAR (not VESSEL_NAME). Data warnings: Crew_Pymts in this year contains both crew and captain payments. Captain_Pymts is null but retained for the cost data application reasons. Table 2.1: VCS_COMMON_VARIABLES_MV METADATA Variable Name Type Description Nullable Survey Years Notes STRATA VARCHAR2(100) Gear and vessel length (either above the average vessel length for this gear group or below) for data stratification Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 Not a survey question but used for sample stratification SURVEY_MODE NUMBER(1) Mode for which the survey was completed (0-online response; 1 - mail response) Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA VESSEL_NAME VARCHAR2(80) Name of the vessel Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA COMMENTS VARCHAR2(4000) Comments from the survey participant recorded at the end of the survey Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA HULLNUM VARCHAR2(30) Official vessel registration number Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA SURVEY_YEAR NUMBER(4) Year survey data pertains to Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA GEAR_TYPE VARCHAR2(40) Primary gear type based on majority revenues from the last year active (Trawl, Gill Nets, Longline, Pots and Traps, Handgear, Dredge, Other) Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA VESSEL_AND_PERMITS_VAL NUMBER(9) The value of the vessel and fishing permits including equipment, fishing gear, permits, and fishing history Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA YEAR_ACQUIRED NUMBER(4) Year vessel owner acquired the vessel Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA OWNER_TYPE VARCHAR2(30) Type of ownership for the selected vessel (corporation, sole proprietorship, s corporation, sole proprietorship, other.) Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA OWNERS_NUM NUMBER(2) Number of owners of the selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA VESSEL_CONDITION_ACQUIRED VARCHAR2(50) Vessel condition when acquired: New or Acquired from Previous Owner Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA HAULOUT CHAR(1) Was the vessel hauled out in the year queried for any reason? (Y/N) Yes 2011, 2012 NA HAULOUT_FREQ VARCHAR2(100) Frequency of haul-out events (every year, every other year, every x years, every xx months). This also includes values from “other” given that they often fit the descriptions listed. Note, if a participant failed to provide the number of years or months, they will render as X or XX. Yes 2011, 2012 NA HAULOUT_COST NUMBER Haul-out costs incurred in the year queried Yes 2011, 2012 NA RMUI_ENGINE_EXP NUMBER Total annual propulsion engine rmui costs for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 *RM and UI were asked separately for each sub cost category so they are summed to get a combined RMUI value RMUI_DECK_EQPT_EXP NUMBER Total annual deck equipment and other machinery rmui costs for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 *RM and UI were asked separately for each sub cost category so they are summed to get a combined RMUI value RMUI_HULL_EXP NUMBER Total annual hull rmui expenses for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 *RM and UI were asked separately for each sub cost category so they are summed to get a combined RMUI value RMUI_GEAR_EXP NUMBER Total annual fishing gear rmui expense cost for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 *RM and UI were asked separately for each sub cost category so they are summed to get a combined RMUI value RMUI_ELECTRONICS_EXP NUMBER Total annual wheelhouse electronics rmui cost for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 *RM and UI were asked separately for each sub cost category so they are summed to get a combined RMUI value RMUI_PROCESS_REFRIG_EXP NUMBER Total annual processing/refrigeration rmui cost for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 *RM and UI were asked separately for each sub cost category so they are summed to get a combined RMUI value RMUI_SAFETY_EQPT_EXP NUMBER Total annual safety equipment rmui cost for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 *RM and UI were asked separately for each sub cost category so they are summed to get a combined RMUI value UI_COST NUMBER Total summed upgrade costs (when applicable) Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 2011: individual cost categories provided for propulsion engine, deck equipment/other machinery, hull, fishing gear, wheelhouse and gear electronics, processing/refrigeration, safety equipment; 2012: same format/categories as 2011 plus an “other” category; 2015: asked for one total cost for all categories combine (same categories as 2011); 2022 and on: RM and UI were not asked for separately RM_COST NUMBER Total summed repair and maintenance costs (when applicable, see comment) Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 2011: individual cost categories provided for propulsion engine, deck equipment/other machinery, hull, fishing gear, wheelhouse and gear electronics, processing/refrigeration, safety equipment. Haul-out cost asked separately; 2012: same format/categories as 2011 plus an “other” category; 2015: asked for one total cost for all categories combine (same categories as 2011). Haul-out cost not asked; 2022 and on: RM and UI were not asked for separately. Haul-out cost included as a RMUI variable. RMUI_COST NUMBER Total summed upgrade and improvement and repair and maintenance costs (when applicable, see comment) Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 RM and UI asked separately in 2011, 2012, 2015 but can be summed by adding variables UI_COST and RM_COST. MOORING_FEES NUMBER(9) Total annual mooring/dockage fees for the selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA PERMIT_FEES NUMBER(9) Total annual state and Federal Permits and/or License Renewal Fees for the selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA VES_INSURANCE_COST NUMBER(9) Vessel insurance cost of the selected vessel including premium paid for hull and/or P&amp;I insurance Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA VES_INSURED_MONTHS NUMBER(2) Number of months selected vessel was insured Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 NA FUEL_COST NUMBER Total annual fuel cost for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 Includes oil and filter for 2011 and 2012 BAIT_COST NUMBER Total annual bait cost for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 NA FOOD_COST NUMBER Total annual food cost for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 NA ICE_COST NUMBER Total annual ice cost for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 NA CATCH_HANDLING_COST NUMBER Total annual catch handling cost such as auction, lumping, grading, shipping etc. for selected vessel Yes 2011, 2012 2012 includes the cost of sales representatives CAPTAIN_STATUS VARCHAR2(30) Captain type for the majority of trips taken; (Examples: Mostly Hired Captain, Mostly Owner-operated, Split Evenly [split evenly between hired captain and owner-operated] No Trips This Year, Other) Yes 2011, 2012, 2015 The “split evenly” and “no trips” options were only provided in 2015 survey. 2011 and 2012 only had mostly owner-operated, mostly hired captain, and other as selection options. CREW_PURCHASES_DESC VARCHAR2(2000 BYTE) Other items that are purchased by crew Yes 2011, 2012 NA BOAT_PCT NUMBER Boat’s percent of gross revenue if share payment system is used Yes 2011, 2012, *2015 *This question was asked in 2015, but the survey form did not print correctly such that no responses were recorded for this question. CREW_PCT NUMBER Crew percent of gross revenues if share payment system is used Yes 2011, 2012, *2015 *This question was asked in 2015, but the survey form did not print correctly such that no responses were recorded for this question. CAPTAIN_PCT NUMBER Hired captain’s percent of gross revenues if share payment system is used Yes 2011, 2012, *2015 *This question was asked in 2015, but the survey form did not print correctly such that no responses were recorded for this question. QUOTA_DAS_PYMTS NUMBER Quota or DAS lease-in costs including estimated value of